search:dotnet+efcore:entity framework co.content:
- Install EF Core using the command: `dotnet add package Microsoft.EntityFrameworkCore`
- For .NET 6, use the latest version of EF Core by running: `dotnet add package Microsoft.EntityFrameworkCore --version 7.0.0`
- Configure DbContext in your project:
  ```csharp
  public class MyDbContext : DbContext
  {
      public DbSet<MyEntity> MyEntities { get; set; }

      protected override void OnConfiguring(DbContextOptionsBuilder optionsBuilder)
      {
          optionsBuilder.UseSqlServer("YourConnectionStringHere");
      }
  }
  ```
- Use migrations to manage database schema changes:
  ```bash
  dotnet ef migrations add InitialCreate
  dotnet ef database update
  ```
- Key configuration options in `appsettings.json`:
  ```json
  "ConnectionStrings": {
    "DefaultConnection": "Server=(localdb)\\mssqllocaldb;Database=MyDb;Trusted_Connection=True;"
  }
  ```
- Use the DbContext in your services or controllers to interact with the database.
